  <assemblage>
    <title>Definitions: Parameter and Statistic</title>
    <p>The term <term>parameter</term>, before considered the process probability, is also used to refer to a numerical characteristic of a population. We will continue to denote population parameters with Greek letters, for example <m>\pi</m> or <m>\mu</m> for a population proportion or population mean, respectively.</p>
    
    <p>A <term>statistic</term> continues to be the corresponding number but calculated from sample data. We denote the statistics for a sample proportion and a sample mean by <m>\hat{p}</m> and <m>\bar{x}</m>, respectively.</p>
  </assemblage>

